Document: Using MultiMeshInstance
Path: godot/tutorials/3d/using_multi_mesh_instance.rst
Summary: This section explains how to randomize the rotation around the up axis of a source mesh using MultiMeshInstance.

Randomizing the rotation around the up axis of the source mesh. This technique allows for creating variations in mesh orientation while maintaining alignment along the vertical axis, useful for generating natural-looking distributions of objects like grass, rocks, or trees in 3D scenes. The implementation typically involves modifying the rotation values in the MultiMeshInstance's transformation data, ensuring that the Y-axis (up vector) remains consistent across all instances. This approach preserves the integrity of the mesh's vertical alignment while introducing randomness in horizontal rotation, creating visually diverse arrangements without disrupting the overall structure.
---CHUNK---
