Document: Using MultiMeshInstance
Path: godot/tutorials/3d/using_multi_mesh_instance.rst
Summary: How to use MultiMeshInstance to place multiple mesh copies on a target surface in Godot 3D.

Amount controls how many mesh instances are placed over the target surface. Select the target surface in the scene tree (e.g., a landscape node). Set the source mesh to the object you want to duplicate. Adjust parameters like density, rotation, and scale as needed. Click "Populate" to generate multiple copies of the source mesh across the target surface. If satisfied with the distribution, delete the original source mesh instance. Note: The final visual result depends on parameter settings and surface geometry. To refine the placement, repeat the process with adjusted values.